      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why O-Words Are Valuable in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>O might only be worth 1 point, but it has a special relationship with X that no other vowel can match. OX (9 points for 2 letters) is one of the highest-scoring two-letter words in the game, and the OX- prefix opens up a whole family of high-value words: OXIDE, OXBOW, OXYGEN, OXIDIZE. This makes O one of the most profitable vowels when X is in play.</p>
      <p>Beyond the X partnership, O combines with Z for words like OOZY (16 points), OZONE (14 points), and the massive OXIDIZE (24 points). O also forms the prefix OUT- which extends into dozens of useful words. The vowel's abundance (8 tiles) means you'll hold it frequently — knowing the premium O-words ensures you never waste it on a low-scoring play when better options exist.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Playing O-Words</h2>
      <p>O is a vowel that rewards players who know its power partnerships. Here's how to maximise your O-word scoring:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>OX is your two-letter weapon:</strong> At 9 points for just 2 letters, OX is devastatingly efficient. On a triple-letter square under X, it scores 25 points. Always look for OX placement opportunities.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Learn the OX- family:</strong> OXIDE, OXBOW, OXLIP, OXCART, OXYGEN, OXIDIZE — these all start with the OX power combination. When you have O+X, scan for board positions that support these longer words.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Use OUT- as a prefix:</strong> OUTFOX (16 points), OUTWIT, OUTPLAY — the OUT- prefix extends many verbs and often reaches premium squares due to the extra length.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Dump excess O tiles quickly:</strong> With 8 tiles in the bag, drawing multiple O's is common. Double-O words like OOZY (16 points), OOH, and OOMPH help clear O-heavy racks profitably.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>O + Z for bonus plays:</strong> OOZY, OZONE, and OXIDIZE combine O with Z for premium scoring. If you hold both O and Z, prioritise these combinations over playing them separately.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Essential O-Word Patterns</h2>
      <p>These O-word families deliver consistent scoring and are easy to remember under competitive time pressure:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>OX- words:</strong> OX, OXO, OXY, OXIDE, OXBOW, OXLIP, OXCART, OXYGEN, OXIDIZE — the most productive O-word family by far</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>O + NYX/RYX:</strong> ONYX (14 points) and ORYX (14 points) are both 4-letter words with impressive scores — remember these animal/mineral words</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>OUT- words:</strong> OUTFOX, OUTWIT, OVERTAX — the OUT/OVER prefix pattern unlocks dozens of plays when you need to extend towards premium squares</span></li>
      </ul>

